d 'SIC_TO_FF': module to convert SIC codes to Fama-French industry classifications
d
d	 sic_to_ff converts Standard Industrial Classification
d (SIC) codes to Fama-French	industry classifications. The
d command supports all major Fama-French industry    classification
d schemes: FF5, FF10, FF12, FF17, FF30, FF38, FF48, and FF49.	
d The command accepts both numeric and string SIC codes. String SIC
d codes are    automatically converted to numeric values.
d Non-numeric strings (e.g., "XXXX") are    treated as missing.   
d The Fama-French industry classifications are widely used in
d empirical accounting and    finance research to group firms by
d industry. These classifications are based on	  four-digit SIC
d codes and are maintained by Kenneth R. French on his data library
d    website. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: SIC codes
d KW: Fama
d KW: French
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20251210
d
d Author: Kelvin Law,   Nanyang Technological University
d Support: email klaw@@ntu.edu.sg
d
f sic_to_ff.ado
f sic_to_ff.sthlp
